        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(copilot): tolerate missing runtime state API during plugin registration",
        "body": "Fixes #94516\n\n## Summary\n\nWhen the host runtime does not expose the state API (`openSyncKeyedStore`), the copilot plugin previously threw `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined`. Added optional chaining (`api.runtime.state?.openSyncKeyedStore`) and a `typeof` guard.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`api.runtime.state.openSyncKeyedStore(...)` assumed `state` is always present. Some runtime configurations omit the state API surface.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/copilot/index.ts`: Check `api.runtime.state?.openSyncKeyedStore` before calling\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Copilot plugin now registers gracefully even without runtime state API.\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e '...'\nCopilot plugin module: ✅ loads correctly\nRegister without state: ✅ no error\nHarness registered: true\n```\n\nBefore fix: `api.runtime.state.openSyncKeyedStore(...)` → `TypeError`\nAfter fix:  `api.runtime.state?.openSyncKeyedStore` → registers without session store\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end with a live Copilot runtime lacking state APIs.\n\n## Risk\n\n- [x] Backwards compatible (null check only)\n- [x] No behavior change when state IS available\n\nCloses: #94516",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94516-copilot-state-optional",
